{
  "stem": "18778.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I remember we spent-- my father had a few marks left.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We were allowed to take per person 10 marks with us. 10 marks translated into dollars, I think about $4.50, plus our clothes on our back, the steamer trunk.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we had sent furniture to the United States as well as to Cuba.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then I think they got some scrip so they could spend some money on board ship.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I remember having a 50 pfennig piece in my pocket.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I gave it to the-- the-- the-- guy who was letting us through, the customs man who-- who kind of was supposed to examine us that we don't have-- smuggle anything.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But he really was very kind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I-- I said, oh, I have this 50-cent piece here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he says, well, go buy yourself something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Other people complained that they were mistreated by the customs people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We didn't have such a-- an experience.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we-- we had a cabin right across from the purser.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We traveled-- there were two classes, first and second class.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We start with first class and we had a cabin, just the three of us, to ourselves.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "The was a luxury liner.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And this was quite a revelation to a 10-year-old, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And that was an adventure for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we embarked.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the ship left on Saturday, the 13th of May.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the band played a song that they usually play when the cruise left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, this is a cruise ship between New York and Havana.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they-- and since it was a German ship, they always played this little song, a little folk song, 'Must I leave my little town.' Wasn't the right thing to do.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
